arguments.prompt:
You are building a Blazor Web App for a university course catalog. The project already exists at `/tmp/sv-f8810de91f36490b8383db9a39e6bd02/UniversityCourseCatalog` created from the `dotnet new blazor` template with `--interactivity Server`. It uses .NET 11 preview with Bootstrap CSS already included.

## What to build

### 1. Data Model & Service (`Models/` and `Services/`)

Create `Models/Course.cs` with:
```csharp
namespace UniversityCourseCatalog.Models;

public class Department
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Code { get; set; } = "";
    public string Name { get; set; } = "";
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
    public List<Course> Courses { get; set; } = new();
}

public class Course
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string CourseCode { get; set; } = "";
    public string Title { get; set; } = "";
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
    public int Credits { get; set; }
    public string Schedule { get; set; } = "";
    public string InstructorName { get; set; } = "";
    public string InstructorBio { get; set; } = "";
    public int DepartmentId { get; set; }
    public string DepartmentName { get; set; } = "";
    public bool IsFeatured { get; set; }
}

public class EnrollmentRequest
{
    public string StudentName { get; set; } = "";
    public string StudentId { get; set; } = "";
    public int CourseId { get; set; }
}
```

Create `Services/CatalogService.cs` — an in-memory data service with realistic seed data:
- At least 5 departments (Computer Science, Mathematics, Physics, English, History)
- At least 3-4 courses per department with realistic titles, descriptions, schedules, credits, instructor names/bios
- Mark ~4 courses as featured
- Methods: `GetDepartments()`, `GetDepartment(int id)`, `GetCourses(string? search, int? departmentId)`, `GetCourse(int id)`, `GetFeaturedCourses()`, `SubmitEnrollmentRequest(EnrollmentRequest request)` (returns a Task<bool>)

Register it as a singleton in `Program.cs`.

### 2. Pages

**Home.razor** (`/`): 
- Hero section with university name and tagline
- "Featured Courses" section showing featured courses as Bootstrap cards (title, department, credits, link to detail)
- "Departments" section with links to the courses page filtered by department

**Courses.razor** (`/courses`): Interactive server-rendered page.
- Search box (text input) and department dropdown filter
- Filterable list of courses displayed as a table or card grid
- Each course links to its detail page
- Use `@rendermode InteractiveServer` so search/filter is interactive

**CourseDetail.razor** (`/courses/{id:int}`):
- Full course info: title, code, department, credits, schedule, description
- Instructor section with name and bio
- "Enroll Now" button/link to the enrollment page

**Enroll.razor** (`/enroll`):
- Standard HTML form with fields: Student Name, Student ID, Course selection (dropdown of all courses)
- Support pre-selecting a course via query string `?courseId=X`
- On submit, call the service and show a success message
- Use `@rendermode InteractiveServer`

**Departments.razor** (`/departments`):
- List all departments with descriptions
- Each links to `/courses?departmentId=X`

### 3. Navigation

Update `NavMenu.razor` to show:
- Home
- Courses  
- Departments
- Enroll

Remove Counter and Weather links. Update the brand to "University Course Catalog".

### 4. Layout updates

Update `MainLayout.razor` — change the top-row link to say "University Intranet" instead of "About" (keep it as a placeholder `#` link).

### 5. Remove template pages

Delete `Counter.razor` and `Weather.razor`.

### 6. Styling

Update `wwwroot/app.css` — add some custom styles to make it look like a university site. Keep it clean and professional. Use a blue/navy color scheme. Don't remove existing styles needed by the layout; add your custom styles at the end.

### 7. Program.cs

Add:
```csharp
builder.Services.AddSingleton<CatalogService>();
```
with the appropriate `using` directive.

### Important notes
- Use `@rendermode InteractiveServer` ONLY on the Courses and Enroll pages (they need interactivity for search/filter and form handling). Home, CourseDetail, and Departments can be static SSR.
- For the Enroll page, use standard Blazor `EditForm` with an `OnValidSubmit` handler.
- Make sure all `@page` directives are correct.
- After creating everything, run `dotnet build` to verify it compiles.
- The project path is `/tmp/sv-f8810de91f36490b8383db9a39e6bd02/UniversityCourseCatalog`

